        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-14T14:31:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, I personally am not very thrilled about putting more %s in these strings. My take is that they are already hard enough to read without it. If the sksl variable were set up in a different file I would agree with passing the string in, but since this is a short file and it\u0027s all contained within here, I still feel like improved readability is quite valuable.\n\nJust curious what you mean by passing a string around to the functions? Who would pass this string to the functions?",
      "parentUuid": "4fb2f10a_b1731dfc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 98,
        "startChar": 42,
        "endLine": 98,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "e35a43a69b0fea2b721ff548e84917eb2395257b",
